Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{some}, season with @salt{some} and @pepper{some}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, sandwich each @British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with the bottom of a #saucepan{} or a #rolling pin{} until it's 1-2 cm thick.

Crack the @egg{1} into a #medium bowl{} and whisk. Put the @breadcrumbs{50%grams} into another medium bowl, then season with the @salt{1/4%tsp}(for breadcrumbs) and pepper.

Dip the chicken into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{some} to coat the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

Once hot, carefully lay the chicken into the pan and fry until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes} on each side. Adjust the heat if necessary.

Transfer the chicken to a baking tray and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. Discard the oil from the chicken pan.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once the chicken is in the oven, wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and pop it back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{some}.

Once hot, lay in the @British streaky bacon{4%rashers} and fry until crispy and brown, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Transfer to a plate lined with #kitchen paper{} and set aside for serving.

== Buns ==

Just before you're ready to serve, halve the @burger buns{2} and pop into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

When everything's ready, spread the @burger sauce{60%grams} over the bun bases and lids.

Top the bun bases with the fried chicken, then the crispy bacon and some @wild rocket{20%grams}. Sandwich shut with the bun lid.

Serve your ultimate fried chicken and bacon burger with the wedges and some @mayonnaise{3%tbsp} on the side for dipping.

Enjoy!